🧤 Assistive Glove System for Healthcare Monitoring and Patient Communication
Overview

The Assistive Glove System is an IoT-enabled healthcare wearable designed to help patients communicate their needs through simple hand gestures while simultaneously monitoring vital health parameters. The system uses an ESP32 microcontroller, flex sensors, a pulse sensor, a DHT11 temperature and humidity sensor, a buzzer, and the Blynk IoT platform for real-time monitoring and alerts.

This project is particularly useful for elderly patients, physically challenged individuals, and patients with limited speech or mobility, allowing them to convey messages through finger gestures and enabling caregivers to monitor their health remotely.

Features
🖐 Gesture-Based Communication

Flex sensors attached to the glove detect finger movements and translate them into predefined messages.

Gesture	Message
Thumb	Help Needed
Index Finger	Need Water
Middle Finger	I Need Food
Ring Finger	Please Call the Doctor
Pinky Finger	I Want to Use the Washroom
Thumb + Index	I'm OK
Ring + Pinky	I'm in Pain
Index + Middle	I'm in Pain, Let Me Rest

All messages are sent instantly to the Blynk IoT application.

❤️ Health Monitoring

The glove continuously monitors:

Heart Rate (BPM) using Pulse Sensor
Body Temperature using DHT11
Humidity Monitoring

Real-time sensor values are displayed on the Blynk dashboard.

🚨 Emergency Alert System
If heart rate exceeds the predefined threshold (120 BPM), an alert notification is sent through the Blynk application.
An emergency buzzer can be remotely controlled through the mobile application.
📱 IoT Connectivity

Using the Blynk IoT platform, caregivers can:

Monitor patient health remotely
Receive emergency notifications
View gesture-based messages
Control the buzzer remotely
